 ## [Unreleased]
 
+### Added
+- **Prompt integrity gate for --light pipeline mode** (Issue #731): `/implement --light` now enforces the HARD GATE: Prompt Integrity for --light Batch Issues before STEP L2 (planner), preventing silent prompt compression that degrades agent output quality. New `prompt_integrity.py` library provides `record_prompt_baseline(agent_type, prompt)`, `validate_prompt_word_count(agent_type, prompt)`, `get_prompt_baseline(agent_type)`, and `get_agent_prompt_template(agent_type)` functions called by the coordinator before each agent invocation. Minimum threshold enforced: 80 words of template text per agent prompt. Planner, implementer, and doc-master prompts in STEP L2-L4 all include explicit `Prompt word count validation: this prompt must contain >= 80 words of template text...` instructions to agents, with FORBIDDEN section covering "Sending any agent a prompt with fewer than 80 words of template text", "Summarizing, condensing, or paraphrasing the planner output before passing it to the implementer", and "Invoking agents with only a skeleton prompt without the required context pasted in". 19 regression tests in `tests/unit/commands/test_light_mode_prompt_integrity.py` validate prompt template word counts and gate presence. `docs/BATCH-PROCESSING.md` updated to document the light pipeline's prompt integrity requirements.
+
 ### Added
 - **Adaptive replanning for implementer blocking signals** (Issue #730): New `blocking_signal_classifier.py` library provides three-tier classification of tool-execution errors into RECOVERABLE (ModuleNotFoundError, FileNotFoundError, ImportError, AttributeError, command not found), STRUCTURAL (SyntaxError, IndentationError, TabError), and NOT_BLOCKING. `classify_blocking_signal(error_output)` returns a `BlockingSignal` dataclass with `signal_type`, `error_name`, `error_detail`, and `suggested_action`. `format_mini_replan_directive(signal, *, cycle)` formats a structured `[MINI-REPLAN cycle N/2]` directive for the implementer. `sanitize_error_for_directive()` truncates and strips newlines to prevent log injection. Implementer agent gains a new "HARD GATE: Mini-Replan on Blocking Signals" section requiring a structured corrective-action cycle (identify → determine action → apply → re-run → evaluate) instead of blind retries, with escalation after 2 failed cycles. Mini-replan cycles are separate from the existing retry budget (Issue #708). 22 unit tests in `tests/unit/lib/test_blocking_signal_classifier.py`. `docs/AGENTS.md` implementer entry updated. `docs/LIBRARIES.md` gains entry 86. `docs/ARCHITECTURE-OVERVIEW.md` library count updated to 189.
 
